U.S. President Joe Biden delivered his first State of the Union address Tuesday. He used the opportunity to condemn Russian President Vladimir Putin. But in the Russian-Ukrainian conflict, the United States is not an innocent bystander, even adding fuel to the fire. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Guan Xin analyzes the U.S. stance on the Russia-Ukraine conflict -- it is actually diverting attention and covering up its own economic problems.